# Architecture Rules

## Component Structure
- Every new UI component MUST be placed in its own file under `components/` (not inline in page.tsx)
- Components must use named exports, never default exports (except page.tsx and layout.tsx which Next.js requires as default)
- All component props must be defined as a named `type` (not inline), suffixed with `Props` (e.g., `type HistoryPanelProps = { ... }`)

## State Management
- Any reusable stateful logic MUST be extracted into a custom hook under `hooks/`
- Custom hooks must be prefixed with `use` and placed in their own file (e.g., `hooks/useProcessingHistory.ts`)
- Never use `any` type — all state must be fully typed

## Styling
- Use only Tailwind utility classes — no inline styles, no CSS modules, no styled-components
- Follow the existing color palette: slate-900/950 for text, sky-600 for primary actions, emerald for success states, red for errors
- All interactive elements must have visible focus states using Tailwind's `focus:` variants

## File Organization
- Shared TypeScript types must live in `types/` directory with descriptive filenames
- Utility/helper functions must live in `lib/` directory
